      &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.hellomagazine.com/tags/sustainability/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sustainable&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; beauty isn&amp;#39;t just about the ingredients listed on the box, or how the
        packaging is made, it&amp;#39;s also about looking at the amount of &amp;#39;new&amp;#39; products shoppers need to buy and how brands can help us shop savvier. Every brand has a different ethos and a different set of rules they abide by but
        refillable beauty is the future - it&amp;#39;s popping up so much more now and soon it&amp;#39;ll just be the norm.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Earlier this year, just before &lt;strong&gt;2021&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;World Earth
        Day,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Jackie Bauer from &lt;a class=&quot;aff_text&quot; href=&quot;http://go.skimresources.com/?id=130574X1592710&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hairstory.com%2F&quot; rel=&quot;sponsored&quot;
        title=&quot;hairstory&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hairstory&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; spoke at the &lt;strong&gt;Sustainable Beauty Summit&lt;/strong&gt;, and said: &amp;quot;It&amp;#39;s about making decisions on how things come into the world, rather
        than dealing it with it when you&amp;#39;re trying to get rid of it. It&amp;#39;s overconsumption. It&amp;#39;s crazy, and I&amp;rsquo;m a culprit, too. But it&amp;#39;s to try and reduce as much as we can. Try to reduce, try to reuse. For us,
        especially, that&amp;rsquo;s the most effective of the three Rs. The more we reuse, the less you consume.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;She added: &amp;quot;The idea that plastic literally disappears once in the ocean or littered
